  "explanation": "The defendant is a first-time offender who committed a non-violent financial crime and has demonstrated remorse and an intent to make restitution by partially repaying the embezzled funds. While embezzlement is a serious breach of trust, a long prison sentence is disproportionate given the amount embezzled and the lack of a criminal history. The outburst from the spectator is irrelevant to the judicial sentencing process. A sentence of 8 months is sufficient to hold the defendant accountable while allowing for rehabilitation.",
  "verdict": 8
}
